Durban- A 50-year-old woman is fighting for her life in a Durban hospital after she was shot in the stomach during a robbery at her Malvern home on Wednesday night. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, KwaZulu Natal police spokesperson, said four armed gunmen had entered the home just after 8pm. Zwane said they allegedly shot the woman and fled the scene. "The suspects fled the scene after the incident and it is not clear whether they took anything from the house. Police are still compiling a report. The woman was taken to the hospital.Â  Malvern police are still searching for the suspects," he said. Garrith Jamieson, the Rescue Care paramedics spokesperson, said the woman was shot in the abdomen was treated at the scene and rushed to a hospital. A case of attempted murder and house robbery was opened at Malvern police station. In a separate incident, a 78-year-old man was held up in his home by three men brandishing knives in Kloof said Zwane. They threatened him and demanded cash, jewellery and other goods. Zwane said the suspects took some goods from the bedroom before they fled the scene. No arrest had been made and the matter was under investigation. A case of house robbery was opened at Hillcrest police station. Daily News